<P>
   MYRON _ Court apparance in federal amateur athletics
investigation. Myron Piggie is denied bail in a court appearance
today after Tom Grant testifies that the former amateur coach
threatened him. Piggie still makes no comment, but his family
releases a statement. By Mark Morris and Katie Funk. Will move in
``a'' category.
</P>
<P>
   MISSOURI _ The Supreme Court today agreed to decide whether
Missouri and other states can require congressional candidates to
support term limits for members of Congress or be labeled an
opponent on the election ballot. The court said it will consider
reviving Missouri's voter-approved measure, thrown out by lower
courts on grounds it unlawfully forced candidates to speak on the
subject or be punished. The justices' decision is not expected
until sometime in 2001, too late for the congressional elections in
November. By Kevin Murphy. Will move in ``a'' category.
BUSINESS OFFERINGS
</P>
<P>
   FUNDS _ With the stock market in turmoil, where are the best
places now to invest your money? For most, the answer is still the
stock market. By Mark Davis. Will move in ``f'' category.
