collaboration between architects and acousticians has put the
science of acoustics to the test, with two major new successes in
Tokyo. The halls in question are the 1,632-seat concert hall of the
multipurpose complex called Tokyo Opera City, and the 1,810-seat
opera house of the adjacent New National Theatre. Both have
acoustically daring designs, yet both have been praised by
musicians who have performed in them. By James Glanz.
