Horatio Alger: Humble but deserving little pill makes good,
transformed after years of plodding fever and headache duty into a
powerful, life-saving heart drug. Three decades into its glamorous
second career, though, it turns out that aspirin is not such a
straightforward super hero of a pill after all. It has proved to be
an immensely complicated medication, with unsuspected dimensions to
both its powers and its limitations. By Abigail Zuger.
