<HEADLINE>
KENTUCKY DERBY UPDATE 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By RON INDRISANO  
 c.2000 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   A look at five of the top contenders for the Kentucky Derby, to
be run May 6 at Churchill Downs:
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL; 
FUSAICHI PEGASUS &QC;
</P>
<P>
   Breeding: Mr. Prospector-Angel Fever (Danzig). Owner: Fusao
Sekiguchi. Trainer: Neil Drysdale. Jockey: Kent Desormeaux. Last
race: Won Wood Memorial at Aqueduct Saturday. Next race: Kentucky
Derby.
</P>
<P>
   Comment: Dazzled in New York after dominating in California.
Imposing physical specimen is unquestionably the one to beat in the
Run for the Roses. We'll see how he and his connections hold up as
the pressure builds. Is he Arazi, or is he Affirmed?
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL; 
THE DEPUTY &QC;
</P>
<P>
   Breeding: PetardiaGB-ManfaithIre (Last TycoonIre). Owner: Team
Valor Stable and Gary Barber. Trainer: Jenine Sahadi. Jockey: Chris
McCarron. Last race: Won Santa Anita Derby April 8. Next race:
Kentucky Derby.
</P>
<P>
   Comment: Began career sprinting on turf in England. Came to
Santa Anita for 3-year-old campaign and won dirt debut. Proved he
is genuine by finishing less than a length behind Fusaichi Pegasus
in San Felipe March 19. Went on to win $1 million Santa Anita Derby
in a very professional performance under excellent handling by
McCarron.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL; 
WAR CHANT &QC;
</P>
<P>
   Breeding: Danzig-Hollywood Wildcat (Kris S). Owner: Majorie and
Irving Cowan. Trainer: Drysdale. Jockey: Jerry Bailey. Last race:
Second in Santa Anita Derby. Next Race: Kentucky Derby.
</P>
<P>
   Comments: Won first three starts, then ran second to The Deputy,
beaten a length after taking a short lead, in Santa Anita Derby.
Appears to have a world of talent and should only improve with
additional training. Runs right on the pace but does not have to be
in front to do his best.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL; 
HIGH YIELD &QC;
</P>
<P>
   Breeding: Storm Cat-Scoop The Gold (Forty Niner). Owner: Bob and
Beverly Lewis, Michael Tabor, and Mrs. John Magnier. Trainer: D.
Wayne Lukas. Jockey: Pat Day. Last race: Won Blue Grass at
Keeneland Saturday. Next race: Kentucky Derby.
</P>
<P>
   Comment: Has experience, having run 12 times, eight as a
2-year-old. Always tries hard, grinding it out in the first flight,
and has been in the money 11 times (4-4-3). The only time he was
off the board, he was roughed up at the break. The Lewises,
racing's top ambassadors, and Lukas combined to win last year's
Derby with Charismatic.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL; 
CAPTAIN STEVE &QC;
</P>
<P>
   Breeding: Fly So Free-Sparkling Delite (Vice Regent). Owner:
Michael Pegram. Trainer: Bob Baffert. Jockey: Robbie Albarado. Last
race: Third in Santa Anita Derby. Next race: Kentucky Derby.
</P>
<P>
   Comment: Has 11 career starts (4-0-5) and finished with good
energy in the Santa Anita Derby. Is another who is consistent and
can turn it on late. Has not won this year, with three straight
thirds, but seems to be going in the right direction. Baffert and
Pegram combined to win 1998 Derby with Real Quiet, and Baffert also
trained 1997 Derby winner Silver Charm, who was owned by the
Lewises.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;  _The second five: Aptitude, Impeachment, More Than Ready,
Anees, Mighty.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Compiled by Ron Indrisano
</P>
