   WASHINGTON NEWS (``w'' category)
</P>
<P>
   GIULIANI-POLICE-SHOOTINGS (Washington) _ Reps. Charles Rangel
and Jerrold Nadler, D-N.Y., urge the Justice Department to
investigate New York Mayor Rudolph Giuliani's release of damaging
information about victims of shootings by city police officers. In
the latest incident, the mayor released juvenile and adult arrest
records of an unarmed man named Patrick Dorismond, killed by
undercover police last month. By AUSTIN ZALKIN. Story will also be
filed in the POLITICAL NEWS (``p'' ) category.
</P>
<P>
   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MEANS-COLUMN (Washington) _ It was sad to watch the grubby
protesters who tried unsuccessfully this week to recreate the
turbulent '60s with garbled complaints against the World Bank and
International Monetary Fund. The demonstrators brought the city to
a temporary halt but were no match for well-behaved cops. Forget
it, kids. You don't have the right stuff and you don't have a
universal cause. By MARIANNE MEANS.
</P>
