A0459 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r e BC-MIRACLE-MAKER-REVIEW-     04-18 0307
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MIRACLE-MAKER-REVIEW-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
THIS LIFE OF JESUS HAS FEET OF CLAY
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
(Eds: Fact box below; `tonight' refers to Sun., Apr. 23) 
Our rating: 2{ stars 
By DAVID KRONKE 
c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``The Miracle Maker'' brings us the Life of Christ in the same
medium that transformed Gumby into a children's icon, Claymation,
mixed intermittently (and irritably) with inferior other styles
(probably farmed out to other animators in order to meet some
deadline or budgetary constraint).
</P>
<P>
   The cast of voices _ led by Ralph Fiennes as Jesus, and
including Julie Christie (playing Mary Magdelene, who's not a
prostitute here, just a little crazy), William Hurt (who, even
though his mug's nowhere in sight, !ital!still!off manages to
overact), Ian Holm, Richard E. Grant and so on _ underscores the
intended level of reverence surrounding this project. And at times,
the tableaux created are visually impressive. Particularly the
crucifixion, but then, every filmmaker tends to do a good job with
the crucifixion; if you can't make that stirring, you don't belong
in the business.
</P>
<P>
   On the other hand, the story is delivered with a reverence
bordering on bloodlessness; kids may enjoy the animation, but
there's nothing that fresh here that parents haven't sat through
countless times before. One imagines the brainstorming session:
``How !ital!hasn't the story of Jesus been told?'' Stay tuned for
next year's sock-puppet version; it really couldn't be any
kitschier than this.
</P>
<P>
   _____ &QL; 
The show: ``!bbox!The show: ``The Miracle Maker'' &QL; 
What: The Life of Christ, Claymation-style. &QL; 
The stars: Voices of Ralph Fiennes, Julie Christie, William Hurt,
Richard E. Grant, Ian Holm, Alfred Molina, Miranda Richardson,
David Thewlis. &QL; 
Where: ABC (Channel 7) &QL; 
When: 7 tonight.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
