<HEADLINE>
SUPERMAN IS SOMETIMES NOT SO SUPER
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q: Did the PEZ company ever make a Superman PEZ dispenser? I've
looked all over eBay with no luck.
</P>
<P>
   _ S.B., via the Internet
</P>
<P>
   A: Despite rumors to the contrary among collectors, there has
never been a Superman PEZ dispenser, according to ``Collecting
PEZ'' author David Welch.
</P>
<P>
   ``It would end up being pretty plain,'' a collector wrote on the
Internet discussion group alt.food.pez. ``Batman, Wonder Woman,
Hulk and Spiderman have distinctive heads or masks ... Superman
just looks like any other guy from the neck up.''
</P>
<P>
   A Washington artist creates made-to-order PEZ dispensers using
casting plaster and modeling clay for $28 to $36. Characters
include Superman, Mr. Natural, Captain Crunch and 40 other figures.
For more information, write to Drew Becker, Box 638, Point Roberts,
WA 98281, or visit the Web site
ourworld.compuserve.com/homepages/rumpusroom.
</P>
<P>
   Incidentally, eBay was founded by Pierre Omidyar in 1995 to
provide a place where his girlfriend could buy PEZ dispensers. More
than 450,000 new items are now auctioned each day on the Web site,
which has 7.7 million registered users.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Where can I find replacement toothbrushes for a SenSonic
electric toothbrush?
</P>
<P>
   _ H.P., Fort Worth
</P>
<P>
   A: Westside Appliance and Electronics in Fort Worth sells a
two-pack of replacement brushes for $18.99, and they are also
available at some Service Merchandise stores.
</P>
<P>
   Westside Appliance is at 5115 Wellview Ave., north of McCart
Avenue and S.W. Loop 820. Call 923-0263 for more information.
</P>
<P>
   SenSonic toothbrushes are manufactured by Teledune Water Pik. To
find the closest stores that carry the company's products, call
(800) 525-2774. You can also buy the brushes on the Web at
www.waterpik.com.
</P>
<P>
   Q: What's Thalia Assuras doing these days since being bumped
from ``CBS This Morning'' for Bryant Gumbel and ``The Early Show''?
I can't stand him at all.
</P>
<P>
   _ V.R.D., Worcester, Mass.
</P>
<P>
   A: Assuras is keeping busy at CBS _ she's co-anchor of ``The
Saturday Early Show'' with Russ Mitchell and works as a Saturday
anchor and correspondent for ``CBS Evening News With Dan Rather.''
</P>
<P>
   The London, Ontario, native has been with CBS News since 1997,
co-hosting ``CBS This Morning'' for five months last year. She
previously was an overnight anchor for ABC's ``World News Now.''
</P>
<P>
   Write to her in care of CBS, 524 W. 57th St., New York, NY
10019.
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com)
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
