<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-18 16:46 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A0583 &Cx1f; tad-z
u w BC-COKE-RALLY19-COX     04-18 0553
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-COKE-RALLY19-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    GROUP RALLIES TO PUBLICIZE RACE BIAS SUIT AGAINST COCA-COLA
 &HT;    Moving in (w) Washington and (f) financial categories.
 &HT;    By ISMAIL TURAY Jr.
 &HT;    c.2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ Chanting slogans of outrage, nearly 50 current and
former Coca-Cola employees held a rally Tuesday on Capitol Hill to
publicize a discrimination lawsuit against the company and pressure
Coke officials to settle the suit quickly.
</P>
<P>
   The event was part of a five-day, four-city ``Ride for Corporate
Justice'' tour that is also aimed at raising public awareness of
