to employment discrimination in corporate America, said the
organizers, the Atlanta-based Committee for Corporate Justice.
</P>
<P>
   The federal lawsuit, filed by eight current and former
employees, alleges that Coca-Cola has discriminated against blacks
in pay and promotions. The plaintiffs are seeking class-action
status so they can represent about 2,000 current and former black
Coke employees in the United States.
</P>
<P>
   The company has denied the allegations and has fought efforts to
make the suit a class-action case. Phone calls to Coke headquarters
were not returned Tuesday, but company spokesman Ben Deutsch said
