<P>
   TEN-UGA-WOMEN _ ATHENS, Ga. _ The Georgia women's tennis team
has completed an unbeaten season in SEC play, including a victory
over previously unbeaten Florida, and enters the conference
tournament this weekend as the favorite. The man behind the team's
success is coach Jeff Wallace, who has led the team to the nation's
No. 3 ranking. Wallace has recruited several talented players to
Athens, including No. 1 singles player Aarthi Ventkasen and
All-American Marissa Catlin, but hasn't received much recognition
for leading the team to the nation's elite. (Towers, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 14.
