<P>
   PURCHASEWISE _ ATLANTA _ BellSouth Corp. on Tuesday added to its
portfolio for small business customers, announcing a service that
aims to smooth the transition to electronic business. (kanell,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 8.
</P>
<P>
   EARNINGS-CCE _ ATLANTA _ Coca-Cola Enterprises, the Coke
system's largest bottler, cut its net loss nearly in half in the
first quarter, meeting Wall Street estimates. Tuesday, the company
reported a net loss of $35 million, or 8 cents a share, compared
with a loss of $62 million, or 15 cents a share in the year-ago
period. (Seward, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   EARNINGS-COKE _ ATLANTA _ For the second consecutive quarter,
Coca-Cola reported a loss of 2 cents a share after taking one-time
charges totaling 24 cents a share, or $680 million. The company
said Tuesday it lost $58 million in the first quarter after
spending $275 million, or 8 cents a share, on its massive
reorganization that will eliiminate 5,200 jobs worldwide. It also
spent $405 million, or $16 cents a share, to write down its excess
bottling capacity in India. Without those non-recurring items, the
company would have earned 22 cents a share on an ongoing basis,
beating the consensus estimate of analysts by a penny. (Unger,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 20.
</P>
<P>
   EARNINGS-DELTA _ ATLANTA _ Delta reports quartlery earnings.
(Thurston, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   DOW-MAIN _ ATLANTA _ The stock market correction may or may not
be at its bottom, but either way many strategists regard last
week's selling as a ``wakeup call'' to investors to bemore careful
where they put their money. The buying so far this week indicates
that investors are looking for high-quality stocks whether
technology or blue chips. The many frivolous dot-com stocks that
moved up on the Internet frenzy will fend for themselves and
probably fall by the wayside, some analysts say. (Walker, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   DOW-EXEC _ ATLANTA _ Everybody it seems has jumped on the stock
options bandwagon, real estate firms, law firms and now executive
search firms are asking for warrants in high tech startups as part
of their commissions when they land a high tech client a big fish.
In this volatile market are people backing off of the stock
options, warrant kick? (Joyner/Ritzler, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 18.
</P>
<P>
   COKE-RALLY _ WASHINGTON _ A group seeking ``a quick and
equitable settlement'' of a discrimination lawsuit brought by black
employees of Coca-Cola Co. holds a rally Tuesday at the Capitol.
(Turay, Cox News Service). 18. WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Moving in (w) Washington and (f) financial categories.
</P>
<P>
   LONG-DISTANCE _ When BellSouth started talking seriously about
offering long-distance, it was the largest of seven regional Bells,
William Clinton was just starting his second term, Newt Gingrich
was riding high and hardly anyone had heard of Monica Lewinsky.
Many things have changed, but BellSouth is still talking about
long-distance. (Kanell, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   MONEYTALK _ This column will not move today.(Ezell, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
