   COXNET WHEELS 0415: 2000 KIA SPORTAGE -- It's little, loud and
generally viewed as being crude and underpowered, but the
Korean-built Kia Sportage has some noteworthy pluses, including a
strong record in off-road racing. The Sportage, available in two-
and four-wheel drive with two trim levels, is built to be cheap,
but start adding options and the bottom line can pass the $20,000
mark. (DeVault, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) Art includes 4-column
color photo of the 2000 Kia Sportage and a 2-column color photo of
the SUV's interior.
