   NATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   ROCKCITY _ LOOKOUT VALLEY, Tenn. _ Rock City barns _ a classic
form of roadside advertising born in the Deep South _ enter the
digital age on Tuesday. One of the famous roadside ``See Rock
City'' barns, in Lookout Valley (at base of Lookout Mountain), gets
painted with a new slogan: See www.seerockcity.com. This is a PR
experiment by Rock City to see if the family-run attraction should
repaint the 80 barns that remain from what once was a network of
900 stretching as far north as Michigan and as far west as Texas.
(Pousner, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 5-7 with photo from Rock
City
</P>
<P>
   CIVILRIGHTS-ISLAM _ WHITE HALL, Ala. _ State and federal
governments are planning to build an interpretive center in White
Hall, Alabama, to commemorate major events of the civil rights
movement. But the government's plan pales in comparison to a
proposal for a $47 million rural Islamic complex for the tiny town
drawn up by accused cop killer Jamil Abdulla Al-Amin. (Davis-Suggs,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 35.
</P>
