   AIRPORT-NOISE (Los Angeles) _ More than 20 years after the idea
was proposed, the Los Angeles City Council on Tuesday took the
first step toward controlling noise at Van Nuys Airport by voting
to ban additional noisy Stage II jets and pursue a phase-out of the
facility. By Rick Orlov. (Will move in the ``n'' California news
