   RIGHT SIDE TOP:
</P>
<P>
   MARKET (New York) _ With corporate earnings soaring, investors
flooded back into United States stocks Tuesday for the second
straight day, retracing much of the ground lost last week. By Alex
Berenson.
</P>
<P>
   (With graphics.)
</P>
<P>
   (Will move by 8:30 p.m.)
</P>
<P>
   RIGHT SIDE BOTTOM:
</P>
<P>
   MERRILL-HSBC (New York) _ HSBC and Merrill Lynch form a joint
venture that will offer online banking and brokerage services to
customers outside the United States. Each company will provide up
$1 billion in start-up capital. The services _ stock trading,
checks, debit cards, cash management and financial planning _ will
be aimed at customers with $100,000 to $500,000 in net assets. By
Patrick McGeehan.
</P>
<P>
   (Will move by 9 p.m.)
</P>
