   WORKPLACE-BLIND-CONSULTANT (Undated) _ Blind people can't easily
tell if a job candidate is white or black, thin or obese, plain or
pretty. So if they should happen to assess an applicant's
professional qualifications, they might well focus on a more
mundane matter: Is she actually suited for the job? That is, in
essence, the question that Herbert Greenberg, 70 years old and
blind since he was 10, has been helping managers answer for the
past 39 years. By Geoffrey Brewer.
