<TEXT>
<P>
   Here are the stories New York Times editors are planning for
Page 1, Wednesday, April 19. The N.Y. Times News Service Night
Supervisor is Pat Ryan; phone: 888-346-9867 or 212-556-1927;
e-mail: patryan(at)nytimes.com.
</P>
<P>
   TOP
</P>
<P>
   Lead story:
</P>
<P>
   SCOTUS-DEATH-PENALTY (Washington) _ The Supreme Court sets aside
the death sentences of two convicted murderers in Virginia,
indicating in two separate decisions that despite the sharp
restrictions imposed on federal courts by a 1996 law, federal
judges still have a significant role to play in reviewing the
quality of justice administered by the states. By Linda Greenhouse.
(The story has moved in ``w'' news file.) 1,500 words.
</P>
<P>
   Top center 3-column photo reefer:
</P>
<P>
   VIETNAM-PHOTOGRAPHERS (Hanoi, Vietnam) _ Twenty-five years after
the Vietnam War ended, a new visual record is emerging from
thousands of photos, little known outside Vietnam, taken from the
communist perspective. By Seth Mydans. (The story has moved in
``i'' news file.) 1,600 words.
