   DRUG-ZYVOX (Washington) _ The FDA approves a drug that is
considered an important new weapon in the fight against antibiotic
resistant germs. The drug, Zyvox, is the first in a new family of
antibiotics, and the first medicine in more than 40 years to treat
a potentially lethal strain of staphylococcus that is on the rise.
By Sheryl Gay Stolberg. (Scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET in ``a''
news file.)
</P>
<P>
   OKLAHOMA-BOMBING (Oklahoma City) _ The bombing of the federal
building here five years ago Wednesday helped create an identity
for a state that had little outside its own borders. From the ruins
and shattered lives emerged a picture of the Heartland, of
neighbors pulling together to help each other. Some people, like a
local businessman and National Guardsman who now runs an institute
on terrorism, have a new focus. By Jim Yardley. (Scheduled to move
by 9 p.m. ET in ``a'' news file.) 900 words.
