 &QL; 
STADIUM (Phoenix) - The Arizona Cardinals football team finally
scores
</P>
<P>
   on a stadium finance bill, winning a tough battle in the Arizona
House in the waning hours of the regular session. The bill, which
is likely to be signed by Gov. Jane Hull, is destined for the Nov.
7 ballot, where Maricopa County voters will get the ultimate say on
whether to raise taxes on hotel beds and rental cars to help build
