<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; Cheryl Shuman-Theo &LR; , who says she is a ``former international
fashion model'' and nowadays calls herself ``optician to the
stars,'' has announced ``Starry Eyes,'' her new line of glasses
``identical to the stars' original designs in hit films and
television shows.''
</P>
<P>
   The first collection, which may be seen in June on the Web at
 &LR; www.StarryEyes.com &LR; , will include frames similar to those in
``Erin Brockovich,'' ``Wonder Boys'' and ``Mission Impossible II.''
Shuman-Theo's glasses have appeared in ``The Terminator,'' ``When
Harry Met Sally ...,'' ``Jurassic Park'' and ``Evita'' (``Don't Cry
for Me, Myopia'').
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; LITERARY ASIDES &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _Tarzan didn't have a beard because ``vine sliding is hell on
your testosterone output,'' says  &UR; Matt Buka &LR; . The  &UR; Edgar Rice &LR; 
 &UR; Burroughs &LR;  books, however, describe him teaching himself to shave
with his father's hunting knife because he didn't want to look like
an ape. ``Almost daily, he whetted his keen knife and scraped and
whittled at his young beard to eradicate this degrading emblem of
