<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-18 20:33 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A0774 &Cx1f; ttj-z
u s BC-BKN-BARKLEY-HNS &LR;      04-18 0649
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKN-BARKLEY-HNS </SLUG>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By JONATHAN FEIGEN  
 c. 2000, Houston Chronicle  
PHOENIX _ There were so many gifts that Charles Barkley said he has
been given. With his final night on an NBA court a day away, he
thought of the first 16 years and all it brought him.
<TEXT>
<P>
   He gives thanks every night, he said, for the joys, the fame,
the money. He has met presidents and kings. Nothing, even the
championship he will leave the game without, could make his life
richer.
</P>
<P>
   But tonight at Compaq Center the Rockets will try.
</P>
<P>
   Barkley was cleared to play the final game of his unique and
spectacular career tonight, giving him the chance to leave the
game, if not on top, upright and celebrated. His career was
declared over when he ruptured his left quadriceps tendon Dec. 8 in
Philadelphia. But when his rehabilitation went faster than
expected, he said he wanted only to be able to enjoy a few final
moments.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't think anybody has had a better life than me,'' Barkley
said. ``People talk about how I didn't win a championship. I don't
see a championship making my life any better. I pray every night,
and I say, `I don't know why you chose me, but thank you.' My life,
I feel like, is unbelievable.
</P>
<P>
   ``I told the Rockets nobody owes me anything: `I think you have
taken care of me long enough.'
</P>
<P>
   ``I know they're going to have a Charles Barkley lookalike
contest and they're going to show a video. I told them that's the
most I want them to do. Nobody owes me anything. I owe you guys
everything.
</P>
<P>
   ``Basketball doesn't owe me anything. I owe everything in my
life to basketball, everything. I'm 37 years old. I'm rich beyond
my wildest dreams. I have great material things. I've been all over
the world, and it's all because of basketball.''
</P>
<P>
   But the Rockets have prevailed upon Barkley to allow a postgame
tribute tonight. There will be a halftime lookalike contest. Fans
will be given Barkley placards and face fans to provide a festive
feeling. A video the Rockets produced celebrating Barkley's career
will be shown.
</P>
<P>
   After the game, the I Am the Warrior video, the first NBA
Entertainment music video, will be shown. Barkley's family and
teammates will be brought back to the floor. The Grizzlies,
including former teammates Othella Harrington, Michael Dickerson
and Brent Price, will be invited to join them.
</P>
<P>
   Rockets coach Rudy Tomjanovich, vice president Carroll Dawson
and several teammates will speak. Rockets teammates and the
organization will present gifts.
</P>
<P>
   But Barkley said the greatest gift he could receive tonight is
just the chance to play. He had hoped to play about 10 minutes
Tuesday night in Phoenix. But there was concern that even a brief
appearance in Phoenix could keep him from playing in Houston and
could diminish his farewell game.
</P>
<P>
   Barkley said his leg was about 70 percent of its previous
strength and that he will be limited in what he would even try to
do.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't want to do anything stupid,'' he said. ``My friends
think I'm nuts. But they understand it's a big deal to me. I don't
want my last memory to be getting carried off a basketball court.
It's that simple. I can't go out and do anything crazy. The last
thing I want to do is hurt myself and have to rehab again.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's just something I need to do, to play my last game and
walk off the court. I don't have anything to prove. It's been a
great 16 years. You have to understand what it would mean for me
just to play a little bit. A basket would be nice. But
psychologically, it would be a great thing for me.
</P>
<P>
   ``It will be very special. I have my mom and grandma and about
20 of my really good friends coming in tomorrow. I want them to be
there. They're all excited. I've got the bigwigs at Nike coming in.
I've got great friends from all over the country. It's going to be
a great night.''
</P>
<P>
   $$$
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-04-18-00 2033EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
