<HEADLINE>
2 KILLED IN MICHIGAN AT HIGH-RISE FOR ELDERLY  

</HEADLINE>
   c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   LINCOLN PARK, Mich. _ A former country music singer shot and
killed two women Tuesday and wounded another person after he was
accused of sexual harassment and verbal abuse in a meeting with the
authorities at a public housing high-rise for the elderly, the
police said.
</P>
<P>
   The shootings came just minutes after housing officials at the
Lincoln Park Seniors Tower confronted the accused gunman, Kenneth
R. Miller, about his neighbors' accusations, said his son, Kenneth
Miller Jr.
</P>
<P>
   The younger Miller said his father, 56, had been battling
depression and ``taking pills for his nerves.''
</P>
<P>
   Miller was arrested four hours after barricading himself in
another tenant's apartment with a .22-caliber rifle after the
shootings, the police said.
</P>
<P>
   Lincoln Park is about 15 minutes south of downtown Detroit.
</P>
<P>
   One of the victims was identified as Marilyn Higgins, 64, a city
housing commissioner, who was making her weekly delivery of
cookies, cakes and breads to the building's 110 tenants, said
Thomas Baize, president of the Lincoln Park Housing Commission.
</P>
<P>
   The other victims were not immediately identified.
</P>
</TEXT>
