<P>
   BC-U.N.-SANCTIONS-NYT (moved on Monday, April 17)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, April 17,
about a decision by the United Nations Security Council to review
its policy on sanctions misstated the flight number of the Pan
American jet that was blown up over Lockerbie, Scotland, in 1988,
leading to sanctions on Libya, since suspended. It was Flight 103,
not 101.
</P>
