<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-CISCO-SBC-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
CISCO AND SBC EXPECT ALLIANCE 
 
</HEADLINE>
  c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Cisco Systems, the data networking company based in San Jose,
Calif., is expected to announce on Wednesday that it has entered
into a multibillion-dollar alliance with SBC Communications, which
is based in San Antonio.
</P>
<P>
   Executives at the two companies said that SBC, the nation's
biggest local phone company, would be among the largest buyers of
Cisco's routers and switches that are used to build the Internet's
infrastructure. Tom McGrath, president of SBC DataComm, would not
disclose the value of the equipment SBC planned to buy.
</P>
<P>
   Cisco and SBC will co-market and co-sell their products and
services _ with SBC selling Cisco equipment to its customers and
Cisco referring customers to SBC. It is one of the first times
Cisco has closely aligned itself with a traditional telephone
company, executives said. It will provide equipment to send
information over five distinct networking platforms, including
digital subscriber lines, which are faster than dial-up modems, and
other services that can transmit data, voice and video.
</P>
<P>
   The two companies will also collaborate on joint research and
product development. The two companies hope to develop products to
make it easier for Internet users to switch between different
Internet service providers, as well as a local area network.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
